WEBVTT

00:01.474 --> 00:08.142
God, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, quiet our hearts as we come to study under your word.

00:09.363 --> 00:15.430
May the words of my mouth and the meditations of our hearts be acceptable and pleasing to you, O Lord, our rock and our Redeemer.

00:16.010 --> 00:16.311
Amen.

00:17.472 --> 00:21.356
So let's read then starting with Haggai chapter two verse six.

00:22.938 --> 00:26.322
Haggai, the prophet says, this is what the Lord Almighty says.

00:26.530 --> 00:31.495
In a little while, I will once more shake the heavens and the earth, the sea and the dry land.

00:32.036 --> 00:35.720
I will shake all nations, and what is desired by all nations will come.

00:36.160 --> 00:39.724
And I will fill this house with glory, says the Lord Almighty.

00:40.364 --> 00:44.329
The silver is mine, and the gold is mine, declares the Lord Almighty.

00:44.949 --> 00:50.535
The glory of this present house will be greater than the glory of the former house, says the Lord Almighty.

00:50.895 --> 00:53.458
And in this place, I will grant

00:53.570 --> 00:56.453
Peace declares the Lord almighty.

00:57.714 --> 01:01.078
And then from Luke chapter one, starting at verse 26.

01:01.298 --> 01:13.191
In the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a town in Galilee, to a virgin pledged to be married to a man named Joseph who was descendant of David.

01:13.751 --> 01:14.993
The virgin's name was Mary.

01:15.773 --> 01:20.178
The angel went to her and said, greetings, you who are highly favored, the Lord is with you.

01:20.994 --> 01:24.738
Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be.

01:25.178 --> 01:30.343
But the angel said to her, do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God.

01:30.904 --> 01:34.487
You will conceive and give birth to a son and you are to call him Jesus.

01:35.148 --> 01:37.870
He will be great and will be called the son of the most high.

01:37.910 --> 01:43.836
The Lord God will give him the throne of his father, David, and he will reign over the house of Jacob forever.

01:44.357 --> 01:45.938
His kingdom will never end.

01:47.099 --> 01:47.720
How will this be?

01:47.780 --> 01:50.002
Mary asked the angel since I am a virgin.

01:50.818 --> 01:57.969
The angel answered, the Holy Spirit will come on you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.

01:58.089 --> 02:01.715
So the Holy One to be born will be called the Son of God.

02:02.897 --> 02:09.888
Even Elizabeth, your relative, is going to have a child in her own age, and she who is said to be unable to conceive is in her sixth month.

02:10.950 --> 02:16.178
For with God, no, sorry there, for no word from God will ever fail.

02:17.218 --> 02:25.010
I am the Lord's servant Mary answered, may your word be according to me, as may it be according to me, may it be to me according to your word."

02:25.030 --> 02:25.892
And the angel left her.

02:27.054 --> 02:33.504
At that time, Mary got ready and hurried to a town in the hill country of Judea, where she entered Zechariah's home and greeted Elizabeth.

02:34.145 --> 02:39.954
When Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting, the baby in her womb leaped for joy, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.

02:40.635 --> 02:44.882
And a loud voice she exclaimed, blessed are you among women, and blessed is the child you will bear.

02:45.378 --> 02:48.302
But why am I so favored that the mother of my Lord should come to me?

02:49.063 --> 02:52.607
As soon as the sound of your greeting reached my ears, the baby in my womb leaped for joy.

02:52.667 --> 02:56.793
Blessed is she who has believed that the Lord would fulfill his promises to her.

02:58.074 --> 03:02.540
And Mary said, my soul glorifies the Lord and my spirit rejoices and God my Savior.

03:03.041 --> 03:07.527
For he has been merciful, the mindful of the humble state of his servant.

03:07.547 --> 03:09.830
From now on, all generations will call me blessed.

03:10.310 --> 03:12.113
For the mighty one has done great things for me.

03:12.173 --> 03:13.234
Holy is his name.

03:13.794 --> 03:17.358
His mercy extends to those who fear him from generation to generation.

03:17.939 --> 03:19.741
He has performed mighty deeds with his arm.

03:19.801 --> 03:22.385
He has scattered those who are proud in their inmost thoughts.

03:22.905 --> 03:25.789
He has brought down rulers from their thrones, but has lifted up the humble.

03:26.450 --> 03:29.373
He has filled the hungry with good things, but has sent the rich away empty.

03:29.934 --> 03:36.622
He has helped his servant Israel, remembering to be merciful to Abraham and his descendants forever, just as he promised our ancestors.

03:37.443 --> 03:40.707
And Mary stayed with Elizabeth for about three months and then returned home.

03:41.007 --> 03:43.090
This is the word of the Lord.

03:43.266 --> 03:44.808
Thanks be to God.

03:48.194 --> 03:51.078
I would like us to think together, to ponder.

03:51.880 --> 04:08.786
Can you think of a time in your life where you were given an announcement that shook up your life, that shook you maybe even to your core, and announcements, maybe a notice, a text, a call that has inexorably changed your life?

04:10.146 --> 04:14.694
I think for many of us, especially in this season of Advent, we probably think children, right?

04:15.455 --> 04:25.431
Whether we're parents, grandparents, great-grandparents, aunts, uncles, cousins, or even just friends with people who have had children pregnancy and birth can drastically change our lives.

04:26.373 --> 04:31.922
I was thinking this morning of a woman who attends the church that Larissa and I went to in Ohio.

04:32.258 --> 04:33.660
This was back in the 70s.

04:33.680 --> 04:36.223
This kind of thing does not happen this quickly now.

04:36.283 --> 04:41.290
But her and her husband were praying about whether they should adopt a child.

04:41.971 --> 04:45.776
And she got a phone call from a doctor that they knew.

04:45.816 --> 04:54.147
And he said, hey, I have somebody who is wanting to surrender their baby because she just can't take care of her.

04:55.009 --> 04:58.393
Can you be here tomorrow morning to pick up a baby to adopt?

04:59.555 --> 05:00.896
And she said, OK, great.

05:00.997 --> 05:02.098
That is the Lord.

05:03.106 --> 05:04.268
hitting me over the head with that.

05:04.368 --> 05:14.364
And so she had to run out and buy everything to furnish a nursery, called her husband after she bought all that stuff, and said, hey, you know how we've been planning to adopt?

05:14.384 --> 05:15.525
Well, the doctor just called me.

05:16.447 --> 05:20.894
And the next day, they had a little baby girl in their house and in their home to raise.

05:22.236 --> 05:25.141
That's a very drastic announcement.

05:25.742 --> 05:28.626
But I'm not just thinking of things like that, though.

05:29.570 --> 05:41.908
I think of getting a letter saying that I had been accepted to go to the college that I wanted to go to, whereas it turns out I'd be set on a path that has led me to my wife, my seminary degree, and ultimately here.

05:41.948 --> 05:49.118
Now remember this, earlier this year, getting a call from Tim saying that you all would like me to move here and be your pastor.

05:50.620 --> 05:53.144
But not all announcements are good, though.

05:53.525 --> 05:54.987
Far, far from it.

05:55.628 --> 05:57.330
I recall getting a call

05:57.474 --> 06:06.566
Right at the end of my first year of undergrad, like two weeks before summer vacation, letting me know that the job that I had been promised this summer before was no longer available.

06:07.868 --> 06:17.361
Many of us have gotten texts or calls or emails from family members or friends to let us know that someone important in our lives has died.

06:18.463 --> 06:26.834
Or we've gotten announcements from doctors to let us know that scans have come back showing cancer or tumors or that a pregnancy is no longer viable.

06:28.578 --> 06:38.168
Now, as you think about a life-changing announcement that you've experienced before, where was God for you in that time?

06:39.210 --> 06:42.994
Was God present with you celebrating and jumping for joy with you?

06:43.054 --> 06:47.919
Was God present in your friends and family members comforting and supporting you?

06:49.361 --> 06:52.904
Did God's presence perhaps feel far away and distant from you?

06:54.506 --> 06:58.130
If you're thinking of a situation that happened long in the past,

06:58.786 --> 07:05.495
In hindsight, where do you see God inviting you to do something because of that event?

07:05.735 --> 07:11.823
Or if you're currently in the midst of something right now, do you have a sense of what God is asking of you?

07:13.245 --> 07:25.682
Now today, we're looking at two world-altering announcements, one from Haggai, the prophet, giving the word of the Lord to return to exiles from Babylon, and one from an angel to a teenage girl.

07:26.786 --> 07:28.508
Now, firstly, we have the prophet Haggai.

07:28.989 --> 07:31.172
This is in the year 520 BC.

07:31.933 --> 07:42.108
If you want a deeper dive into this short book, Pastor Michael did a sermon series on that in the fall of last year, which you can find on our YouTube page or on the podcast feed on our website.

07:42.448 --> 07:54.866
But what I will say here is that Haggai's main thrust of prophecies to compel and encourage these returned exiles from Babylon to begin to rebuild the Lord's temple in Jerusalem.

07:55.938 --> 08:07.372
Now, these exiles as they had returned from Babylon starting to rebuild their lives in their homes, they had grown complacent, even maybe fearful of taking concrete steps to rebuild.

08:08.313 --> 08:18.386
And God, through the prophet Hagai, tells the people that they're wasting their efforts on building fancy homes for themselves while neglecting the Lord's ruined temple.

08:19.106 --> 08:22.530
And God encourages the people as they begin to work on the temple.

08:22.590 --> 08:28.516
And the prophecy that we read today from chapter two comes about one month after they had started construction.

08:29.497 --> 08:37.385
And this prophecy also comes about the time of the feast of booths or the feast of tabernacles.

08:38.065 --> 08:46.354
When the Jewish people were commanded to build temporary structures outside of their homes to dwell and to remember their time wandering in the wilderness.

08:47.138 --> 08:49.040
So think of the symbolism in the imagery here.

08:49.060 --> 08:53.265
There's scaffolding all around the temple as the people have begun to build.

08:53.325 --> 08:58.011
And there are all these temporary tents set up around people's houses.

08:58.912 --> 09:08.543
And Haggai begins this prophecy before our text today by asking the people to look upon the one month of work that they have done on the temple.

09:09.143 --> 09:11.506
And he says to them, does this seem like nothing to you?

09:13.154 --> 09:25.970
They must have been discouraged in their work knowing how long it took to build the original temple in Solomon's day, knowing all the resources it took to build that temple, all the money, all of the labor, all the material.

09:25.991 --> 09:28.113
This is when Israel was at the height of its power.

09:29.495 --> 09:33.921
And now they have nothing but a burnt foundation to work with.

09:33.941 --> 09:38.066
And indeed, it would take them over four years to construct this temple.

09:38.914 --> 09:46.086
And I'm sure as these people were beginning to build it, they knew that it wouldn't be as impressive or fancy as its former iteration.

09:47.869 --> 09:54.880
In this darkness and discouragement, Haggai tells the people that God has promised that His Spirit will be with them.

09:55.782 --> 10:00.690
And God then promises in our text from Haggai today that He will shake all the nations.

10:01.218 --> 10:03.401
And what is desired by all nations will come.

10:03.481 --> 10:05.804
God will fill this house with glory.

10:06.165 --> 10:14.576
And the glory of this present house, which is currently no more than foundations and scaffolding, will be greater than the glory of the former house.

10:15.457 --> 10:19.443
And in this place, I will grant peace, declares the Lord Almighty.

10:21.085 --> 10:24.690
Now what does God mean when he says that he'll shake the nations again?

10:25.986 --> 10:37.597
Well, before this, the Old Testament prophets refer to God shaking the earth, shaking the nations when nations are defeated as in the prophets, Jeremiah Ezekiel's prophecies.

10:38.138 --> 10:47.707
Or when God's presence comes on a space or upon a people as Ezekiel prophesies, God shakes the earth because of his anger.

10:47.747 --> 10:55.154
This imagery of God shaking the earth and the nations is one that announces and proclaims God's ultimate power

10:55.362 --> 10:58.387
over everything, even the mountains and the seas.

11:00.330 --> 11:05.919
That which seems permanent to humans is merely temporary in God's eyes.

11:07.241 --> 11:22.706
This promise of shaking things up then is a promise to God's people that as they rebuild this temple, God promises to fill this temple with His presence even more so than before and to bring all the nations to Him under His banner of peace.

11:23.586 --> 11:31.834
And the shaking of the earth and the nations that has promised in Haggai will bring forth the treasures of all the nations who will bend the knee and worship the Lord Almighty.

11:33.616 --> 11:37.940
Now I presume you can see where it goes from this, especially since we're in Advent and Christmas.

11:38.580 --> 11:42.764
As with everything in Scripture, the book of Haggai and this prophecy points to Jesus.

11:43.705 --> 11:52.914
Now, a key thing about prophetic words in Scripture is they always have a present and a future promise.

11:53.506 --> 12:03.295
So this word from Haggai that God will be with his people that he will shake the nations is a tangible promise for these returned exiles who have begun their work to rebuild this temple.

12:03.776 --> 12:08.640
And as they seek to resolitify their identity as God's people in their land once more.

12:09.441 --> 12:17.489
But this also points us forward to Christ and even to us today as Haggai declares timeless truths about God.

12:18.269 --> 12:20.051
God is present with his people.

12:20.111 --> 12:21.853
God is at work in creation.

12:21.893 --> 12:23.314
God is in control.

12:23.650 --> 12:28.198
and God invites his people to participate in the work that he is doing.

12:29.541 --> 12:33.367
The commenter, Jay Alec Mottier, nicely articulates it like this.

12:33.428 --> 12:48.114
He says, the people of God in their present situation can commit themselves confidently to active involvement in the work of God and can do so without fear that all will come to nothing because the future

12:48.290 --> 12:57.508
is in the hand of God and it will be splendid with richness, full of the presence of the Lord in all of His glory and bringing the blessing of peace.

12:58.189 --> 13:02.898
This future is wholly, entirely God's doing.

13:04.642 --> 13:19.158
So then just after just over 500 years after this prophecy from Haggai, we get another universe shaking announcement from God as God once again promises to be present with his people and invites them into what he is doing in the world.

13:20.439 --> 13:29.849
Now in Luke's gospel, Luke has prepared his readers for something big happening with the announcement in chapter one of the birth of John the Baptist.

13:30.910 --> 13:34.514
If you read this against the book of Genesis,

13:35.170 --> 13:45.746
It hits a lot of the same beats as how God announced to Abraham and Sarah that they would have a son in their old age through whom God would bless all the nations of the earth.

13:46.948 --> 13:59.346
Luke has set this stage in our text today by reminding us of this great story of the people of God, how God through uncommon means has brought about great things for his people and for the world.

13:59.938 --> 14:05.284
But now we are given an announcement about something that is even greater than what has happened before.

14:06.346 --> 14:16.918
Elizabeth, who was the mother of John the Baptist, has a relative, who was a teenager named Mary, engaged to a man named Joseph, who was in the lineage of King David.

14:17.980 --> 14:22.065
Mary and Joseph are from a small village in the northern region of Galilee.

14:23.226 --> 14:29.874
This to this teenage girl, as young as 12 even, in a small town,

14:30.018 --> 14:37.128
probably content, if not excited, to marry into the storied lineage of David and just live a normal, peaceful life.

14:37.869 --> 14:41.934
It is to this girl whom God announces something huge.

14:42.936 --> 14:50.386
She will give birth to the promised Messiah, the Son of God, through whom God will dwell with His people in human form.

14:52.130 --> 15:03.644
The angel Gabriel who brings this announcement to Mary assures her of God's presence and promise by telling her of Elizabeth's pregnancy as proof that God is indeed active and at work in creation.

15:04.706 --> 15:14.157
He even alludes directly to God's promise to Abraham and Sarah because he tells Mary no word from God will ever fail after he announces to her Elizabeth's pregnancy.

15:14.938 --> 15:21.266
In Genesis 18, God asks Abraham and Sarah, is anything too hard for the Lord?

15:21.890 --> 15:27.997
And this after Sarah, someone understandably, laughs at the idea that she would be able to bear a child in her old age.

15:29.499 --> 15:35.146
And so Mary, after hearing this, it hurries down to the hill country of Judea where Elizabeth lives.

15:35.907 --> 15:42.355
And when she gets there, Elizabeth, Luke tells us, was filled with the Holy Spirit and proclaims, blessed are you, Mary, among women.

15:42.435 --> 15:44.017
Blessed is the child you will bear.

15:44.317 --> 15:48.562
Blessed is she who has believed that the Lord would fulfill his promises to her.

15:49.858 --> 16:00.133
And then Mary testifies to God's faithfulness in verses 46 to 55, which contained what is known as the Magnificat, or Mary's song, which we will sing as our song of response.

16:01.275 --> 16:17.458
In the grand tradition of women in the Bible, singing of God's faithfulness, declaring God's promises to his people like Miriam or Hannah, Mary declares God's mercy and faithfulness to her as God dains to look upon a person like her in such a humble state.

16:18.274 --> 16:21.938
But God's promises and faithfulness to Mary are not all that she sings of.

16:21.958 --> 16:30.507
As God has shaken her life with this announcement, the birth of this child will have far-reaching consequences for all peoples on earth.

16:31.387 --> 16:45.522
God will once again shake everything up with the coming of this child, bringing rulers down from their thrones, raising up the humble, giving the hungry food and sending the rich away with nothing, continuing to covenant with his people forever.

16:46.530 --> 16:51.097
as Haggai proclaimed timeless truths about God, so here Mary does as well.

16:52.259 --> 16:55.003
This is consistent with the character of God throughout scripture.

16:55.344 --> 17:01.774
God looks upon the poor and the humble, the unassuming, and he invites them to be a part of his plan for the world.

17:02.976 --> 17:07.563
Abraham was a nomadic herdsman who had no direct heir.

17:08.825 --> 17:14.354
David was the youngest son of his family, so unimportant and unassuming

17:14.594 --> 17:18.961
that he was not invited to attend a family sacrifice with the prophet Samuel.

17:20.003 --> 17:28.676
Now in that account in 1 Samuel, God has this lengthy back and forth with the prophet to convince him to see the world through God's eyes.

17:28.756 --> 17:34.445
God tells Samuel that men look at the outward appearance, but the Lord looks at the inward, at the heart.

17:36.108 --> 17:42.418
So to Mary seems to be of little cosmic importance until this point in her life.

17:43.554 --> 17:48.221
Even everything surrounding the birth of Jesus is humble and quiet.

17:49.583 --> 17:57.295
As we will read on Wednesday and over the next couple of weeks into Christmas tide, God chooses the humble and the poor over the powerful and the proud.

17:58.377 --> 17:58.578
Right?

17:58.638 --> 18:03.165
Who is it that learns first of the birth of the Savior of the world?

18:04.106 --> 18:11.698
It's a group of shepherds, dirty, poor, probably young kids right around Mary's age, if not younger.

18:13.218 --> 18:19.585
Wise men from the east come foreigners, astrologers who do not follow after the God of Israel.

18:21.127 --> 18:24.230
And who is it that ignores the importance of this?

18:25.592 --> 18:28.735
Who is it that instead only thinks of themselves and their power?

18:28.835 --> 18:31.278
It's the king and the religious leaders.

18:33.180 --> 18:42.450
I don't want to get too far ahead of myself and get into what we'll look at together in Christmas time, but God chooses the meek, the humble, the powerless as his people.

18:42.850 --> 18:45.994
that he invites into the work of the world that he is doing.

18:47.035 --> 18:54.125
And it is through this humility that God will topple empires, raise up the lowly and bring the world to him.

18:54.165 --> 18:59.592
This world shaking will bring about God's justice and peace over all the world.

18:59.952 --> 19:04.178
God will bring all nations to him and reign over them in peace.

19:06.306 --> 19:13.697
God invites Mary to be a part of this cosmic design and in great faith she ascents to God's plan for her.

19:14.559 --> 19:16.141
I am the Lord's servant, she says.

19:16.201 --> 19:18.304
May it be to me according to your word.

19:20.568 --> 19:24.273
So what is God announcing to you and I as we read this?

19:26.096 --> 19:35.090
God is announcing to us through Haggai and through the angel, through Mary, through Luke that he has shaken up the world in the past and that he will do it again.

19:35.874 --> 19:43.421
God is announcing that He is with us, Emmanuel, Jesus, the great son of the Most High has come.

19:44.342 --> 19:50.508
Not only has He come, but He has given His life for our sins and has risen from the dead and ascended into heaven.

19:51.709 --> 20:00.637
God has announced to us that He continues to be with us even now through the indwelling presence of the Holy Spirit in our hearts and who is in this space with us.

20:02.319 --> 20:05.842
So what then is God inviting us to do?

20:06.914 --> 20:09.578
What timeless truths do we need to be reminded of?

20:10.881 --> 20:22.320
We have seen from Haggai and from Luke that when God announces something big, he promises to be with his people, promises to shake things up, and then invites his people to be a part of what he's already doing in the world.

20:23.462 --> 20:30.994
God invited the returned exiles of Haggai's time to take part in his work by rebuilding the temple and refounding themselves as his people.

20:32.194 --> 20:38.181
God invited Mary to assent to the Holy Spirit coming upon her so that she would conceive and give birth to the Messiah.

20:39.843 --> 20:45.089
So what does God invite us to do as we read these earth-shaking announcements?

20:45.129 --> 20:59.026
As we look to our Savior, the desire of nations, the King of peace, how are we being invited to serve Him and to work alongside Him for the purpose of God's kingdom here on earth as we await Christ's return?

21:00.610 --> 21:04.354
We are being invited by God to be His church.

21:06.417 --> 21:11.863
We are invited by God to be the bride of Christ, God's body here on earth.

21:11.923 --> 21:16.629
The apostle Peter writes this in 1 Peter 2.

21:16.989 --> 21:27.602
He says, as you come into Him, that is Jesus, the living stone, you also like living stones are being built into a spiritual house to be a holy priesthood.

21:28.226 --> 21:39.296
And you are a chosen people, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, God's special possession, that you may declare the praises of Him who called you out of darkness into His wonderful light.

21:40.638 --> 21:43.440
Once you were not a people, but now you are the people of God.

21:43.600 --> 21:47.144
Once you had not received mercy, but now you have received mercy.

21:49.065 --> 21:58.194
As God's people who live in this already but not yet time between the incarnation and the return of Christ,

21:58.466 --> 22:04.353
We are inheritors of all of these promises that God has made to His people throughout the millennia.

22:05.234 --> 22:27.282
To Abraham and Sarah, to David through Samuel, to these returned exiles through Haggai, to Elizabeth and Mary through Gabriel the angel, these announcements of God shaking the earth and doing great and new things, these promises of God's presence with His people, this invitation to join in the work of His kingdom here on earth, all of these are ours.

22:27.682 --> 22:32.206
because we are God's people.

22:32.226 --> 22:35.830
And that is all well and good, but let's get a little bit practical as we wrap up here.

22:36.571 --> 22:43.978
What are we here in this space being invited to do in this community?

22:45.119 --> 22:53.988
Where are we being invited by God to do the work of his kingdom, to bring an end to division and to unite all peoples under Christ, our king of peace here in Midland?

22:55.829 --> 22:56.530
Thank you, Miles.

22:58.882 --> 23:04.132
That is what we as a church have been asking for the past few years.

23:05.074 --> 23:11.767
This is why we now have our new mission statement, learning to live and love like Jesus has broken people saved by grace.

23:12.067 --> 23:19.762
This is why we have our key values of God's Word and community and integrity and renewal of the mind and service.

23:20.482 --> 23:29.895
This is why the missional deacons and the consistry with your input have discerned that God is calling us to address food insecurity and social needs in our community around us.

23:31.798 --> 23:40.110
This is the discerning question for us as a church as we go forth into the season of ministry guided by our priorities that we have already discerned.

23:42.053 --> 23:47.781
Now, that's not to say that the answer to what is God inviting us to do ends with, well, we've been working on it.

23:47.801 --> 23:48.722
Good job, everybody.

23:49.634 --> 23:50.195
It is good.

23:50.455 --> 23:58.883
It is great that we have been working on discerning these things, but it is also of utmost importance that we continue to seek after God in everything we do.

23:58.903 --> 24:02.706
How does God invite us to live into this world?

24:02.747 --> 24:08.312
How does God invite us to interact with people who we disagree with, who vote differently than us?

24:08.372 --> 24:15.299
How does God invite us to bring about His Kingdom in this fallen chaotic and broken world?

24:17.701 --> 24:18.962
We look to Jesus.

24:19.042 --> 24:19.923
for these answers.

24:20.223 --> 24:23.227
We look to Him, the author and perfecter of our faith.

24:24.709 --> 24:29.815
My friends, brothers and sisters in Christ, as Mary proclaimed, God has done great things for us.

24:30.575 --> 24:33.399
He is merciful to those who seek after His ways.

24:33.679 --> 24:38.625
He has promised to be with us and He has upheld that promise and continues to do so.

24:39.466 --> 24:42.309
He has brought peace to the world through the light of the world.

24:42.369 --> 24:43.871
His Son, our Savior, Jesus.

24:43.911 --> 24:46.514
He has broken into this world with that peace.

24:47.842 --> 24:53.451
It is under his banner of peace that all the nations on earth will come under him.

24:53.911 --> 24:58.158
It is under that banner of peace that we seek to unite all peoples, all nations.

24:59.280 --> 25:16.146
As we seek after where God is calling us to minister, let our hearts sing the words that we have already sung with our voices, O come, desire of nations, bind to all peoples in one heart and mind, bid all our sad divisions cease and be thyself.

25:16.514 --> 25:17.776
our king of peace.

25:18.677 --> 25:19.318
May it be so.

25:19.919 --> 25:20.240
Amen.

25:23.505 --> 25:39.390
As we think of how to respond to this call, as we think about how to respond to God's invitation to us to work with Him in the world and in our community, just have a few things for you to mull over.

25:39.490 --> 25:44.818
Perhaps you want to write them down on the little yellow response slips, take it home, put it in the offering plate.

25:46.402 --> 25:52.970
Is there something tangible that I think God is calling me to do right now?

25:54.172 --> 25:55.493
That could be in our church life.

25:55.533 --> 25:56.615
That could be in our community.

25:56.655 --> 25:57.796
That could be in our families.

25:57.976 --> 26:06.146
Is there something that God is putting on your heart that's something tangible that you can do in the next few weeks?

26:06.167 --> 26:09.010
Perhaps you might think of a praise

26:09.474 --> 26:17.522
for how God has led you through a difficult announcement or a prayer request as you navigate that now.

26:19.864 --> 26:26.250
Perhaps you might think of what it looks like in your life to follow after this desire of nations.

26:26.710 --> 26:29.613
What does it look like for me to bring about God's peace?

26:33.217 --> 26:38.962
Or perhaps, are there ways in which I am hindering God's peace in the world?

26:40.034 --> 26:43.449
through my thoughts, my words, or even my deeds.

26:45.256 --> 26:47.506
If so, what do I need to do to repent of that?

